Here is a multiple-choice question in JSON format.
{
    "question": "Given the Python script below, what portion of the code will not be executed due to being a comment?\n\n```python\n# Initial variable setup\nx = 2\ny = 3\nz = x + y\n\n# Printing the result\nprint(f\"The sum of {x} and {y} is:{z}.\")\n\n# End of code\n```\n",
    "choices": [
        {
            "choice": "print(f\"The sum of {x} and {y} is:{z}.\")",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "x = 2\ny = 3\nz = x + y",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "# Initial variable setup\n# Printing the result\n# End of code",
            "correct": "true"
        }
    ]
}

Are the distractors that are completely unique, or are they similar?
